# Glitch web stack boundaries

## Package roles

- `apps/website` is the real public marketing site.
- `apps/app` is still placeholder scaffolding unless the user explicitly wants product work there.

## Guardrails

- Preserve env-driven Whop links and CTA routing in `apps/website/src/lib/marketing-links.ts`.
- Do not make arbitrary pricing, offer, legal, or marketing-copy changes.
- Do not imply that `apps/app` is a finished product.
- Do not invent an `apps/docs` app; current docs live under `ninjatrader/Glitch/Docs`.

## Validation

- Validate only the affected workspace by default.
- Update local docs or env examples when behavior or required configuration changes.
